WEBVTT

00:01.401 --> 00:03.335
- We're dealing with
a serious condition,

00:03.337 --> 00:04.536
called Immune thrombocytopenia.

00:04.538 --> 00:06.338
- But he can still report
to work, right?

00:06.340 --> 00:07.506
- Not right now.

00:07.508 --> 00:09.475
- What would you think
about us becoming

00:09.477 --> 00:11.076
<i>foster parents to Louie?</i>

00:11.078 --> 00:13.545
- Gabby, we barely have time
for each other.

00:13.547 --> 00:16.482
<i>- I can't get him</i>
<i>out of my head, Matt,</i>

00:16.484 --> 00:19.051
<i>so I'm going to do it</i>
<i>on my own.</i>

00:19.053 --> 00:21.720
- When I'm married,
you break into my house

00:21.722 --> 00:24.056
with flowers and champagne,

00:24.058 --> 00:26.058
and then I'm solo,

00:26.060 --> 00:29.061
and you keep
a safe distance.

00:29.063 --> 00:32.698
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:37.437 --> 00:40.439
<i>[poignant music]</i>

00:40.441 --> 00:48.547
<i>â™ª </i>

00:50.784 --> 00:53.552
- Let's call furlough
for the next six to eight weeks.

00:53.554 --> 00:56.355
- [chuckles]

00:56.357 --> 00:58.090
And go where?

00:58.092 --> 01:00.092
- Right here.

01:00.094 --> 01:02.694
Never leave this spot.

01:02.696 --> 01:05.697
[alarm beeping]

01:05.699 --> 01:13.806
<i>â™ª </i>

01:18.711 --> 01:20.179
Mm.

01:20.181 --> 01:23.348
<i>â™ª </i>

01:23.350 --> 01:26.351
All I'm saying is,
I could get used to this.

01:26.353 --> 01:32.424
<i>â™ª </i>

01:37.230 --> 01:38.831
[engine turns over]

01:44.537 --> 01:47.539
[car departs]

01:47.541 --> 01:50.542
<i>[dark music]</i>

01:50.544 --> 01:58.650
<i>â™ª </i>

02:06.126 --> 02:07.493
- Excuse me,
I have to get going to work.

02:07.495 --> 02:10.896
- Mr. Harvey's got several
people to see this morning.

02:10.898 --> 02:12.898
- Yeah,
what about tomorrow?

02:12.900 --> 02:16.468
- Meetings all day.

02:16.470 --> 02:19.638
Look, I can give you a call
if there's an opening.

02:19.640 --> 02:22.241
- You know,
this isn't about me, right?

02:22.243 --> 02:23.909
There's a kid sitting somewhere
right now

02:23.911 --> 02:26.612
without a family, without
a place to call home, nothing.

02:26.614 --> 02:28.180
- By the time
the children reach us,

02:28.182 --> 02:30.682
they're all that way,
unfortunately.

02:34.587 --> 02:36.255
- Okay...yes,

02:36.257 --> 02:38.223
please give me a call
if you find time for me.

02:38.225 --> 02:40.292
I appreciate it.

02:41.762 --> 02:45.631
- Oh, it's nothing fancy,
just a good DJ, cheap booze.

02:45.633 --> 02:47.466
I need a favor from you,
though.

02:47.468 --> 02:48.500
- Of course you do.

02:48.502 --> 02:50.335
- The liquor license.

02:50.337 --> 02:51.637
You wouldn't believe
the amount of hoop-jumping

02:51.639 --> 02:53.372
you've got to do
to get one of those,

02:53.374 --> 02:55.507
but now that my little brother
works with an alderman...

02:55.509 --> 02:56.909
- No, not a chance.

02:56.911 --> 02:58.610
- I wouldn't have come to you
if this wasn't important.

02:58.612 --> 03:00.512
I'm 15 grand deep.

03:00.514 --> 03:02.381
I'm losing money every day.

03:02.383 --> 03:04.216
Jimmy,
I'm serious.

03:04.218 --> 03:05.384
If I don't get this place
opened up,

03:05.386 --> 03:06.885
I could lose the house.

03:06.887 --> 03:09.488
- Hey...
could you restock the 4x4s?

03:09.490 --> 03:10.489
I think we're running low.

03:10.491 --> 03:11.490
Hey, Danny.

03:11.492 --> 03:12.491
- Hey.

03:12.493 --> 03:13.892
[alarm beeps]

03:13.894 --> 03:17.229
<i>- Truck 81, Ambulance 61,</i>
<i>car accident,</i>

03:17.231 --> 03:19.665
<i>2802 West 47th Street.</i>

03:19.667 --> 03:21.533
- I'll see what I can do.

03:21.535 --> 03:23.769
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

03:23.771 --> 03:26.772
[sirens wailing]

03:26.774 --> 03:30.776
<i>â™ª </i>

03:30.778 --> 03:32.878
<i>[indistinct radio chatter]</i>

03:32.880 --> 03:35.480
- Mouch, Kidd,
check out that smoke.

03:35.482 --> 03:36.481
- Copy that.
- Watch the rig.

03:36.483 --> 03:38.917
- Let's get these people out.

03:38.919 --> 03:43.922
<i>â™ª </i>

03:43.924 --> 03:46.391
- Strike.
Strike.

03:46.393 --> 03:48.527
- [grunting]

03:48.529 --> 03:53.298
<i>â™ª </i>

04:00.473 --> 04:02.774
- Casey.

04:02.776 --> 04:03.775
- Hey.

04:03.777 --> 04:06.245
[metal bar clatters]
You okay?

04:06.247 --> 04:08.880
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

04:08.882 --> 04:11.316
Brett,
let's get a C-collar over here.

04:11.318 --> 04:14.786
- Okay.

04:14.788 --> 04:16.388
Hi, I'm Sylvie.

04:16.390 --> 04:17.489
What's your name?

04:17.491 --> 04:18.690
- Kaylee.

04:18.692 --> 04:21.727
[both grunting]

04:21.729 --> 04:23.729
- Hey, stand up.

04:23.731 --> 04:26.665
- I'm gonna put this
around your neck.

04:26.667 --> 04:28.400
[siren wailing in the distance]
[metal bar clatters]

04:28.402 --> 04:29.668
Does any of that hurt?

04:29.670 --> 04:30.869
- A little.

04:30.871 --> 04:32.904
- Ugh.

04:32.906 --> 04:34.906
Wait.
Stay there.

04:34.908 --> 04:37.609
[siren wailing]

04:37.611 --> 04:39.645
- You feel any pain
in your tummy or your chest?

04:39.647 --> 04:42.481
- No.
- No?

04:42.483 --> 04:44.449
- Yeah, she's loaded.
- Yeah.

04:44.451 --> 04:45.917
Wait there.

04:45.919 --> 04:47.619
- What do we got?

04:47.621 --> 04:48.754
- Mom and dad are sauced.

04:48.756 --> 04:51.490
Had their kid driving.

04:51.492 --> 04:53.492
- Good, good, good.

04:53.494 --> 04:54.760
- Ugh.

04:54.762 --> 05:02.534
<i>â™ª </i>

05:02.536 --> 05:04.870
- Are they gonna--
are they...

05:04.872 --> 05:06.705
Oh.

05:06.707 --> 05:07.973
- Brett.

05:07.975 --> 05:12.577
<i>â™ª </i>

05:12.579 --> 05:14.379
- Jimmy,
seat belt may have given her

05:14.381 --> 05:15.847
a pulmonary contusion.

05:15.849 --> 05:19.451
Need the stethoscope.

05:19.453 --> 05:21.920
Diminished lung sounds
on the left side.

05:21.922 --> 05:23.555
Damn it.
She has a broken rib.

05:23.557 --> 05:25.924
- She might have
a punctured lung.

05:25.926 --> 05:27.693
- The trachea's deviated.
She has a pneumo.

05:27.695 --> 05:28.927
- All right,
let's trauma her to Med.

05:28.929 --> 05:30.395
I'll decompress her en route.

05:30.397 --> 05:31.663
- All right.

05:31.665 --> 05:35.534
<i>â™ª </i>

05:35.536 --> 05:37.869
- Kaylee, Mommy loves you!

05:37.871 --> 05:39.438
- Yeah, real nice work, folks!

05:39.440 --> 05:40.472
You put your daughter
in the hospital!

05:40.474 --> 05:43.408
- Hey, hey, hey, come on.

05:43.410 --> 05:46.945
- Disgusting.

05:46.947 --> 05:48.814
- You all right?

05:48.816 --> 05:50.682
- The world's rough enough.

05:50.684 --> 05:53.652
Your own parents shouldn't be
making it rougher.

05:53.654 --> 05:54.786
I'm--I'm fine.

05:54.788 --> 05:58.724
Just got my dander up,
but I'm fine.

06:02.930 --> 06:05.797
- What the hell
are you doing here?

06:05.799 --> 06:08.400
- I'm on steroids.
I'm not bedridden.

06:08.402 --> 06:10.902
- See, what I heard when they
said "medical leave" was,

06:10.904 --> 06:12.404
"four weeks paid vacation."

06:12.406 --> 06:13.939
- Yeah, shouldn't you be
on a singles tour

06:13.941 --> 06:15.407
of Middle-earth or something?

06:15.409 --> 06:18.410
- Ha, yeah,
I'm here to collect my check.

06:18.412 --> 06:20.412
Hey, Lieutenant, what's up?
- Hey, buddy.

06:20.414 --> 06:23.548
- You know, it's okay
to admit you--you miss us.

06:23.550 --> 06:24.950
- Who's on in relief?

06:24.952 --> 06:26.418
- Malcolm Ferguson.
You know him?

06:26.420 --> 06:27.552
- No.
- Oh.

06:27.554 --> 06:30.622
Ferguson, get over here!

06:35.428 --> 06:38.397
<i>[mellow music]</i>

06:38.399 --> 06:40.165
<i>â™ª </i>

06:40.167 --> 06:41.900
Otis, Ferguson.

06:41.902 --> 06:43.969
Ferguson, Otis.

06:43.971 --> 06:45.637
- Great guy.
You're gonna love him.

06:45.639 --> 06:47.806
- Okay, yeah.
- Yeah.

06:47.808 --> 06:49.908
- H-hey, man, B-Brian.

06:49.910 --> 06:51.810
[knuckles crunch]
Hey, hey...

06:51.812 --> 06:53.445
[clears throat]
Hey.

06:53.447 --> 06:55.080
- The Evanston guy.
Yeah.

06:55.082 --> 06:57.549
Hey, so listen,
that thing that you did...

06:57.551 --> 06:58.583
[whispering]
- [chuckles]

06:58.585 --> 06:59.684
- You did.

06:59.686 --> 07:01.420
Oh!

07:01.422 --> 07:02.554
You're the man.

07:02.556 --> 07:06.425
- Yeah, Connie handpicked him
herself, so...

07:06.427 --> 07:07.559
- Connie?

07:07.561 --> 07:08.960
- Yeah, she's been keeping
a list of CFD's

07:08.962 --> 07:10.562
best floaters for Boden.

07:10.564 --> 07:13.064
Had her eye on Ferguson
for a while now.

07:13.066 --> 07:15.200
Real happy she finally found
a spot for him.

07:15.202 --> 07:17.035
- Mm-hmm.
- Well, temporarily.

07:17.037 --> 07:20.839
It's not like we got ourselves
a Wally Pipp situation here.

07:20.841 --> 07:23.975
[laughter]

07:23.977 --> 07:25.777
- Who's--who's Wally Pipp?

07:25.779 --> 07:27.646
- First baseman
for the 1925 Yankees.

07:27.648 --> 07:30.215
Took a day off with a headache,
got replaced with Lou Gehrig,

07:30.217 --> 07:33.218
who went on to play
2,130 consecutive games.

07:33.220 --> 07:36.688
- But like I said,
you're not him, so...

07:36.690 --> 07:39.858
- Yeah, Connie--
Connie would never replace me.

07:39.860 --> 07:42.027
- Mm, absolutely not.

07:42.029 --> 07:43.094
- Good to see you.

07:43.096 --> 07:44.563
- Yeah.

07:44.565 --> 07:46.965
<i>â™ª </i>

07:46.967 --> 07:48.600
- A child?

07:48.602 --> 07:50.502
- Not just any child.

07:50.504 --> 07:52.704
We pulled him out of
the fire at north Dayton.

07:52.706 --> 07:56.708
- Well, paperwork's done,
aside from a background check.

07:56.710 --> 07:59.644
And I already started
parenting classes.

07:59.646 --> 08:02.581
- All I need is a letter
of recommendation from you.

08:02.583 --> 08:05.684
- What are your chances
of qualifying, realistically?

08:05.686 --> 08:08.487
- Unlikely.

08:08.489 --> 08:11.523
But "unlikely"
doesn't mean "impossible."

08:11.525 --> 08:12.958
- And what if the boy
gets placed somewhere else

08:12.960 --> 08:14.659
in the meantime?

08:14.661 --> 08:18.029
- I just want
what's best for him,

08:18.031 --> 08:23.235
whether that's me
or another foster family.

08:23.237 --> 08:24.870
Where he is now,
the group home,

08:24.872 --> 08:27.138
he deserves better.

08:27.140 --> 08:30.709
And I know
I can give that to him.

08:32.612 --> 08:36.214
I have to try.

08:36.216 --> 08:38.683
- I'll have the letter
for you today.

08:38.685 --> 08:40.719
<i>[stirring music]</i>

08:40.721 --> 08:42.921
- Thanks, Chief.
Thank you.

08:42.923 --> 08:46.725
<i>â™ª </i>

08:46.727 --> 08:47.993
[door opens]

08:47.995 --> 08:50.996
<i>â™ª </i>

08:50.998 --> 08:52.664
- Hey.

08:52.666 --> 08:54.599
- Hey.

08:54.601 --> 08:56.268
- I thought you were
coming over yesterday.

08:56.270 --> 08:57.602
- I know, yeah.

08:57.604 --> 09:00.105
I just got a lot going on.

09:00.107 --> 09:03.308
- And the day before that?

09:03.310 --> 09:06.578
- I've been spending
every free moment at DCFS

09:06.580 --> 09:11.016
trying to find five minutes
to plead my case.

09:11.018 --> 09:15.020
This foster thing,
it's moving forward.

09:15.022 --> 09:18.023
<i>[solemn music]</i>

09:18.025 --> 09:21.226
<i>â™ª </i>

09:21.228 --> 09:22.928
I don't mean for it to come
between us, Matt, but--

09:22.930 --> 09:26.264
- But you're doing this.

09:26.266 --> 09:29.200
- Yeah, I am.

09:29.202 --> 09:33.705
- Okay, then...

09:33.707 --> 09:36.675
good luck.

09:36.677 --> 09:38.810
- Thanks.

09:38.812 --> 09:46.918
<i>â™ª </i>

09:54.927 --> 09:57.128
[knocking]

09:57.130 --> 09:58.863
- Hey.
- Hey.

09:58.865 --> 10:01.933
- Can I get your opinion
on something?

10:04.003 --> 10:06.738
Danny just bought this club,
and he wants me to help him

10:06.740 --> 10:07.973
get his liquor license.

10:07.975 --> 10:10.075
- The after hours thing
in Bucktown?

10:10.077 --> 10:12.243
- What do you mean after hours?

10:12.245 --> 10:14.112
- Been up and running
a few months,

10:14.114 --> 10:15.814
all cash,
under the table.

10:15.816 --> 10:16.982
He trying to take it legit?

10:16.984 --> 10:18.249
- I guess.

10:18.251 --> 10:19.684
I don't know.

10:19.686 --> 10:22.053
He wants me to ask Casey
for a favor.

10:23.789 --> 10:24.956
- I wouldn't.

10:24.958 --> 10:27.258
- Nope,
and that's what I figured.

10:27.260 --> 10:30.128
- Anything else?

10:30.130 --> 10:32.697
Close my door, then.

10:36.802 --> 10:40.238
- Basically, DCFS just wants to
know that I'm not a criminal.

10:40.240 --> 10:42.140
I thought maybe you could
expedite the background check.

10:42.142 --> 10:45.276
Shouldn't be a big deal.

10:45.278 --> 10:46.645
Say something.

10:46.647 --> 10:49.314
- What's Casey think
about all this?

10:50.249 --> 10:51.716
- I'm doing this alone.

10:51.718 --> 10:53.418
- Why?

10:53.420 --> 10:54.853
- Right now,
this is more important

10:54.855 --> 10:57.022
than my relationship,
Antonio.

10:57.024 --> 10:59.958
- What I need from you
is your support, okay?

10:59.960 --> 11:02.827
What I don't need
is your permission.

11:02.829 --> 11:05.830
<i>[tense music]</i>

11:05.832 --> 11:07.032
<i>â™ª </i>

11:07.034 --> 11:08.199
- I'll have
the background check for you

11:08.201 --> 11:09.701
by the end of the day.

11:09.703 --> 11:11.336
- Thank you.

11:11.338 --> 11:19.344
<i>â™ª </i>

11:19.346 --> 11:21.012
- Hey.

11:21.014 --> 11:23.915
- I need you to clarify
a few things for me.

11:23.917 --> 11:25.316
- Okay.

11:25.318 --> 11:27.085
- You still in love
with my sister?

11:27.087 --> 11:28.753
- Of course I am.

11:28.755 --> 11:30.789
- And you know about this
foster situation?

11:30.791 --> 11:33.291
- Yeah.

11:33.293 --> 11:35.927
- Then why the hell is
she doing this on her own?

11:35.929 --> 11:38.396
- She made that call
without me.

11:38.398 --> 11:40.031
- Maybe because you've been
stringing her along

11:40.033 --> 11:41.099
for three years.

11:41.101 --> 11:42.801
- All right, okay.

11:42.803 --> 11:44.035
That's not even close
to what happened, all right?

11:44.037 --> 11:47.205
- You were supposed to
marry her.

11:47.207 --> 11:49.174
Now she's out there
taking this thing on by herself.

11:49.176 --> 11:50.475
- I tried to talk to her.

11:50.477 --> 11:53.211
- That's where you screwed up,
talking.

11:53.213 --> 11:55.447
You either go get her
and make this right for good,

11:55.449 --> 11:57.716
or you leave her the hell alone.

11:57.718 --> 11:59.751
- You want to intimidate
someone, Antonio,

11:59.753 --> 12:01.386
take it back to the 21st.

12:01.388 --> 12:03.822
If you're just giving advice,
then I can tell you.

12:03.824 --> 12:05.824
I don't want it.

12:05.826 --> 12:07.492
[chair clatters]

12:07.494 --> 12:12.197
<i>â™ª </i>

12:26.345 --> 12:29.280
- Gabriela,
what are you doing here?

12:29.282 --> 12:32.784
- I'm...just trying to get in
with Mr. Harvey,

12:32.786 --> 12:34.018
hoping he'll give me a chance.

12:34.020 --> 12:35.453
- Are you on shift?

12:35.455 --> 12:37.021
- Yeah, on my way in.

12:37.023 --> 12:39.023
Just stopped by in case.

12:39.025 --> 12:40.258
I know.
It's a long shot.

12:40.260 --> 12:42.227
- Single mom with a job
like this.

12:42.229 --> 12:44.996
Are you sure you're ready
to foster?

12:44.998 --> 12:48.166
- Never been more sure.

12:48.168 --> 12:50.535
- We have a staff meeting later.

12:50.537 --> 12:52.937
I'll talk to Mr. Harvey,
see what I can do.

12:52.939 --> 12:54.139
- Thank you.

12:54.141 --> 12:57.242
- No promises.

13:04.283 --> 13:06.417
- Come on in,
have a seat.

13:12.525 --> 13:17.162
Gabby asked me for a letter
recommending her to DCFS.

13:17.164 --> 13:19.030
I wrote her a glowing review.

13:19.032 --> 13:22.033
- Thanks, Chief.
- Mm-hmm.

13:22.035 --> 13:26.070
Unfortunately, I'm not sure
how far my words are gonna go.

13:26.072 --> 13:29.073
This is a long, hard road.

13:29.075 --> 13:31.042
- That's exactly
what I'm afraid of.

13:31.044 --> 13:33.411
- Yeah, we both know Gabby.

13:33.413 --> 13:34.913
There ain't no
turning back now.

13:34.915 --> 13:37.415
- Yeah,
she made that perfectly clear.

13:37.417 --> 13:41.586
Well, I believe
everything happens for a reason.

13:41.588 --> 13:43.321
There's no way
that I can send men

13:43.323 --> 13:45.156
running into a burning building
without knowing

13:45.158 --> 13:48.960
that there was some kind of
bigger plan.

13:50.029 --> 13:54.199
You and Gabby,
you've had a tough year.

13:54.201 --> 13:58.970
You've had your wins
and your losses.

13:58.972 --> 14:04.142
Then there's this newfound clout
that you have being an alderman.

14:04.144 --> 14:07.145
<i>[tense music]</i>

14:07.147 --> 14:09.581
<i>â™ª </i>

14:09.583 --> 14:12.584
Maybe there's a reason
for that too.

14:12.586 --> 14:17.422
<i>â™ª </i>

14:17.424 --> 14:20.291
- Hey,
been looking for you.

14:20.293 --> 14:23.962
Did you get a chance
to talk to Casey?

14:23.964 --> 14:25.597
- Look, if you think
I'm bringing my Lieutenant

14:25.599 --> 14:27.432
into this,
you are out of your mind.

14:27.434 --> 14:28.499
- What?

14:28.501 --> 14:30.301
- An after hours club?

14:30.303 --> 14:32.003
That is illegal, Danny.

14:32.005 --> 14:35.039
try dealing with the city
if you get busted.

14:35.041 --> 14:37.442
- I had to make money
to get the liquor license.

14:37.444 --> 14:39.210
- What did you want me to do,
sit on the place

14:39.212 --> 14:41.880
while I'm getting bled dry
on rent not making a dime?

14:41.882 --> 14:46.050
- I wanted you to be legit.
- That's what I'm trying to do.

14:46.052 --> 14:47.452
I'm drowning.

14:47.454 --> 14:49.320
I got Stacy beating me up
every five minutes

14:49.322 --> 14:51.155
asking me why the checking
account is taking on water.

14:51.157 --> 14:53.324
- This is because
you rush into things.

14:53.326 --> 14:55.526
- Are you gonna help me or not?

